3 Sec. 14. 25 MRSA §2923-A, as amended by PL 2011, c. 505, §3, is further amended
4 to read:
5 §2923-A. Requirements of municipalities, plantations, counties or unorganized
6 territories
7 Each municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory that does not have a
8 public safety answering point shall contract with an entity that does have a public safety
9 answering point, which may be the department, for receiving 9-1-1 calls and, as
10 appropriate, directly dispatching emergency services or, through transfer routing or relay
11 routing, passing 9-1-1 calls to public or private safety agencies that dispatch emergency
12 services. If a municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory without a public
13 safety answering point does not enter into such an agreement, the department shall serve
14 as the public safety answering point for that municipality, plantation, county or
15 unorganized territory and the municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory shall
16 pay the department for the provision of those services. Fees received by the department
17 pursuant to this section must be deposited in the Consolidated Emergency Communications
18 Fund established in section 1534. If a fee assessed to a municipality, plantation, county or
19 unorganized territory for services provided pursuant to an agreement under this section or
20 by the department is based in whole or in part on population, the population of the
21 municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory may not include persons held at a
22 correctional facility, as defined in Title 34‑A, section 1001, subsection 6, within the
23 municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory.
24 Sec. 15. 25 MRSA §2923-B, sub-§1, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 186, §1, is amended
25 to read:
26 1. Notice. A public safety answering point shall provide notice to the bureau prior to
27 discontinuing service to a municipality, plantation, county or unorganized territory. A
28 public safety answering point may not provide the notice under this subsection less than
29 one year prior to the date that the public safety answering point discontinues service, unless
30 the bureau finds reasonable grounds to authorize a shorter period of time for the
31 notification. If appropriate, the bureau shall notify the department of the notice of
32 discontinuing service received by the bureau from a public safety answering point.
