21 Sec. 29. 25 MRSA §2930, as amended by PL 2007, c. 504, §1, is further amended
22 to read:
23 §2930. Immunity
24 1. Governmental entity. Subject to all the limitations and exceptions provided under
25 the Maine Tort Claims Act, Title 14, chapter 741, a government governmental entity is
26 immune from tort liability for property damages, bodily injury or death resulting from acts
27 or omissions occurring in developing, establishing, implementing, maintaining or operating
28 the E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system.
29 2. Telecommunications providers. A telecommunications provider assisting in the
30 implementation and operation of the statewide E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system, including, but not
31 limited to, the development, establishment and maintenance of the E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system,
32 is subject to tort liability:
33 A. For property damages, bodily injury or death resulting from any defect in the
34 E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system or inadequacy in the provision of E-9-1-1 9-1-1 service caused
35 by the telecommunications provider's negligent acts or omissions in developing,
36 establishing, implementing, maintaining or operating the E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system, up to
37 a maximum amount for any and all claims arising out of a single occurrence not to
38 exceed $300,000 or the dollar amount that appears in Title 14, section 8105, subsection
39 1, whichever is greater; and
40 B. For property damages, bodily injury or death resulting from any defect in the
41 E-9-1-1 9-1-1 system or inadequacy in the provision of E-9-1-1 9-1-1 service caused
42 by the telecommunications provider's intentional, willful or reckless acts or omissions
Page 10 - 132LR0556(01)

413 in developing, establishing, implementing, maintaining or operating the E-9-1-1 9-1-1
424 system, without limitation on the amount.
